## Stepper Compound Component -- Implementation Plan

### 1. Architecture Overview

The Stepper component follows the exact same compound component pattern as `carousel.tsx`: a custom React context-based component with no Radix UI dependency. It uses two levels of context (Stepper-level and StepperItem-level) to allow child components to derive state from their position in the tree.

**File structure (4 deliverables):**
- `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/stepper.tsx` -- the component
- `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/stepper-demo.tsx` -- the demo
- Insert into `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/_registry.ts` at line 563 (after spinner, before switch)
- Insert into `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/_registry.ts` at line 2124 (after spinner-item, before switch-demo)

